Properties

Optional activationStrategy

activationStrategy: string
  • Defined in node_modules/aurelia-router/dist/aurelia-router.d.ts:169

Add to specify an activation strategy if it is always the same and you do not want that to be in your view-model code. Available values are 'replace' and 'invoke-lifecycle'.

Optional caseSensitive

caseSensitive: boolean
  • Defined in node_modules/aurelia-router/dist/aurelia-router.d.ts:163

When true is specified, this route will be case sensitive.

Optional generationUsesHref

generationUsesHref: boolean
  • Defined in node_modules/aurelia-router/dist/aurelia-router.d.ts:142

Indicates that when route generation is done for this route, it should just take the literal value of the href property.

Optional href

href: string
  • Defined in node_modules/aurelia-router/dist/aurelia-router.d.ts:137

The URL fragment to use in nav models. If unspecified, the RouteConfig.route will be used. However, if the RouteConfig.route contains dynamic segments, this property must be specified.

Optional moduleId

moduleId: string
  • Defined in node_modules/aurelia-router/dist/aurelia-router.d.ts:104

The moduleId of the view model that should be activated for this route.

Optional name

name: string
  • Defined in node_modules/aurelia-router/dist/aurelia-router.d.ts:99

A unique name for the route that may be used to identify the route when generating URL fragments. Required when this route should support URL generation, such as with Router.generate or the route-href custom attribute.

Optional nav

nav: boolean | number
  • Defined in node_modules/aurelia-router/dist/aurelia-router.d.ts:131

When specified, this route will be included in the Router.navigation nav model. Useful for dynamically generating menus or other navigation elements. When a number is specified, that value will be used as a sort order.

Optional navModel

navModel: NavModel
  • Defined in node_modules/aurelia-router/dist/aurelia-router.d.ts:158

The navigation model for storing and interacting with the route's navigation settings.

Optional navigationStrategy

navigationStrategy: function
  • Defined in node_modules/aurelia-router/dist/aurelia-router.d.ts:116

A function that can be used to dynamically select the module or modules to activate. The function is passed the current NavigationInstruction, and should configure instruction.config with the desired moduleId, viewPorts, or redirect.

Type declaration

    • (instruction: NavigationInstruction): Promise<void> | void

    • Parameters

      • instruction: NavigationInstruction

      Returns Promise<void> | void

Optional redirect

redirect: string
  • Defined in node_modules/aurelia-router/dist/aurelia-router.d.ts:109

A URL fragment to redirect to when this route is matched.

route

route: string | string[]
  • Defined in node_modules/aurelia-router/dist/aurelia-router.d.ts:92

The route pattern to match against incoming URL fragments, or an array of patterns.

Optional settings

settings: any
  • Defined in node_modules/aurelia-router/dist/aurelia-router.d.ts:153

Arbitrary data to attach to the route. This can be used to attached custom data needed by components like pipeline steps and activated modules.

Optional title

title: string
  • Defined in node_modules/aurelia-router/dist/aurelia-router.d.ts:147

The document title to set when this route is active.

Optional viewPorts

viewPorts: any
  • Defined in node_modules/aurelia-router/dist/aurelia-router.d.ts:124

The view ports to target when activating this route. If unspecified, the target moduleId is loaded into the default viewPort (the viewPort with name 'default'). The viewPorts object should have keys whose property names correspond to names used by elements. The values should be objects specifying the moduleId to load into that viewPort.
